   <tool name="extract_csrf_token">
-    <description>
-      Extract CSRF token from HTML content.
-      
-      Searches for common CSRF token patterns in HTML forms, meta tags,
-      and JavaScript code. Can automatically store the token in a session.
-      
-      Detected patterns:
-      - Hidden input fields: csrf_token, _csrf, csrfmiddlewaretoken, _token, 
-        authenticity_token, __RequestVerificationToken
-      - Meta tags: &lt;meta name="csrf-token" content="..."&gt;
-      - JavaScript: csrfToken = "...", window.__csrf = "..."
-      - Data attributes: data-csrf="..."
-    </description>
+    <description>Extract CSRF token from HTML.</description>
